{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fb57ac73-9258-4021-8234-6c54fcee344f","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. MSTest v3 **dropped support** for two of your three target frameworks:\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET Framework ≥ 4.6.2** (you're fine there) and **.NET 6.0+** for the modern SDK-style targets. Both `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` are end-of-life and no longer supported.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to update your `TargetFrameworks` to replace those, e.g.:\n\n```\nnet8.0;net462\n```\n\nor if you need multiple modern TFMs: `net8.0;net6.0;net462`.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2c292b94-a02b-47da-8b6f-ff9abc2eeddb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a project that targets:\n- net5.0\n- net462\n- netcoreapp3.1\n\nAnd uses MSTest v2 (2.2.10).\n\nMSTest v3 dropped support for older target frameworks. Let me think about what I know:\n\nMSTest v3 (specifically MSTest 3.x) requires:\n- .NET 6.0 or later for .NET Core/5+ targets\n- .NET Framework 4.6.2 or later (net462 should be fine)\n\nWait, let me be more precise. MSTest v3 dropped support for:\n\n\n- .NET Framework versions older than 4.6.2\n- .NET Core 3.1\n- .NET 5.0\n\nSo the user's `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` targets would be problematic. `net462` should still be supported.\n\nMSTest v3 only supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+ and .NET 6.0+, which means the user's `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` targets are incompatible and would need to be updated to supported versions.","outputTokens":563,"requestId":"4C14:35214E:BD895F:E5FFE4:6A014295"},"id":"57e5a61d-2427-42c9-b6d3-5b1183538419","timestamp":"2026-05-11T02:44:50.266Z","parentId":"a9095150-be82-4a03-8dd6-ef1bed1e1e4b"}
